  "prompt": "What is the best free webDAV service?",
  "response": "There are several free WebDAV services available, each with its own features and limitations. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Google Drive**: While not a traditional WebDAV service, you can use third-party applications to access Google Drive via WebDAV, such as Rclone.\n\n2. **Nextcloud**: If you are open to self-hosting, Nextcloud allows you to create your own cloud storage service with WebDAV support. Many providers offer free tiers, or you can set it up on your server.\n\n3. **OwnCloud**: Similar to Nextcloud, OwnCloud can be self-hosted, providing WebDAV capabilities along with other cloud storage features.\n\n4. **pCloud**: pCloud offers WebDAV access, and while it has free and paid subscriptions, the free tier has limited storage.\n\n5. **Koofr**: Koofr provides a free tier with WebDAV access, allowing users to connect third-party storage providers.\n\n6. **Filestash**: Not a storage provider, but an open-source WebDAV client that can connect to various storage services.\n\n7. **Yandex.Disk**: This is a cloud storage service that also supports WebDAV, allowing limited free storage.\n\nWhen choosing a service, make sure to review their specific terms, storage limits, security features, and compatibility with your devices. If you're looking for a robust solution with lots of features, self-hosting with Nextcloud or OwnCloud might be your best bet.",
